column19:
Welcome to our research survey!



We want to learn more about people's numerical skills. Some of the questions are challenging. We only ask that you try your best. 



On the survey, we will check if people are paying attention. Those paying attention will get an additional bonus payment.



Your answers are anonymous. And only aggregated results will be shown in reports and presentations.



Do you consent to take this survey?

column21: In the BIG BUCKS LOTTERY, the chances of winning a $10 prize are 1%. What is your best guess about how many people would win a $10 prize if 1000 people each buy a single ticket from BIG BUCKS?
column22: A train travels 1 mile in 1 minute and 20 seconds. How many miles will it travel in one hour?
column23: Imagine that we roll a fair, six-sided die 1000 times. On average, how many times will the die come up as an even number?
column24: In a sale, a shop is selling all items at half price. Before the sale, the sofa costs $300. How much will it cost on sale?
column25: A second hand car dealer is selling a car for $6,000. This is two-thirds of what it cost new. How much did the car cost new?
column26: A father is 33 years older than his son. The father is also four times as old as his son. What's the fatherâ€™s age.
